text.section:
Any industrial insured captive insurer that is created under the Product Liability Risk Retention Act of 1981, 15 U.S.C. secs. 3901 et seq., as amended, shall be subject to the following provisions of this chapter and the administrative regulations promulgated thereunder, to the extent applicable and not in conflict with the express provisions of this subtitle:
Subtitle 1--Scope--General Definitions and Provisions;
Subtitle 2--Commissioner of the Department of Insurance;
Subtitle 3--Authorization of Insurers and General Requirements, including but not limited to:
KRS 304.3-400 to 304.3-430; and
KRS 304.3-500 to 304.3-570;
Subtitle 4--Fees and Taxes;
Subtitle 5--Kinds of Insurance--Limits of Risk--Reinsurance, including but not limited to KRS 304.5-120;
Subtitle 6--Assets and Liabilities;
Subtitle 7--Investments;
KRS 304.9-700 to 304.9-759--Reinsurance Intermediary Act;
Subtitle 33--Insurers Rehabilitation and Liquidation;
Subtitle 37--Insurance Holding Company Systems; and
Subtitle 99--Penalties.
